message.content:
1. Intracellular concentrations of adenosine-5’-triphosphate (ATP) are greater than extracellular concentrations.
2. Intracellular concentrations of ATP are 1–10 mM.
3. Extracellular concentrations of ATP are 10–100 nM.
4. The release of ATP from cells is tightly controlled.
